# TubeWatch Design System

## Purpose

This rule defines the global UI design system for TubeWatch.
All pages must follow this system for visual consistency.
The style is Light SaaS UI inspired by Linear.

---

## Background

- Page background: bg-white
- Section panel: bg-gray-50
- Admin sidebar: bg-gray-50

---

## Card

- bg-white
- border border-gray-200
- rounded-xl
- shadow-sm
- padding: p-5 or p-6

Do not use rounded-2xl for cards. Always use rounded-xl.

---

## Typography

Page title: text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900
Section title: text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900
Body text: text-sm text-gray-600
Meta text: text-xs text-gray-500

Do not use font-bold for titles. Always use font-semibold.

---

## Button Hierarchy

Primary action:
- bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white
- rounded-lg px-4 py-2

Secondary action:
- border border-gray-300 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 text-gray-700
- rounded-lg px-4 py-2

Do not use bg-blue-600, bg-gray-900, or bg-black for primary buttons.
The canonical primary color is indigo-600.

---

## Input Focus

- focus:border-indigo-500 focus:ring-1 focus:ring-indigo-500

Do not use blue for focus rings.

---

## Status Badges

Success: bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700
Warning: bg-amber-100 text-amber-700
Error: bg-red-100 text-red-700
Neutral: bg-gray-100 text-gray-600
Admin: bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700

Badge shape: rounded px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-semibold

---

## Table Style

Container: bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl
Header: bg-gray-50 text-gray-500 text-xs font-medium
Row: hover:bg-gray-50
Numbers: tabular-nums
Text overflow: truncate + title attribute for hover

---

## Spacing

Section spacing: space-y-8 or mt-8
Card padding: p-5 or p-6
Card list gap: space-y-4 or gap-4

---

## Page Layout Pattern

Page Header → Status Cards → Main Content → Data Table / Card List → Primary Action

---

## Accent Colors

Progress indicators: bg-indigo-500 or bg-indigo-600
Active state: bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-700
Empty state icons: bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-500

Do not use blue-500 or blue-600 for accents. Use indigo consistently.
